@sguada do you mean I run twice? Run once with **is_training=False** to get a graph def just for inference nodes purpose (stop the process once I get this file), because if I set **is_training=False**, the loss do not goes down, which means the network does not converge.

after I get the graph def file for inference nodes, I still need use the .ckpt file which is created under **is_training=True**, since this .ckpt file contains the correct values for weights.

